THE ALEX JONES SHOW
2009.06.16 Tuesday

Alex talks with 9/11 truth activist Greg Hoover who is suing Glenn Beck, the producers of the Glenn Beck program, and the Fox News Channel for attempting to link truth activists to white supremacist and accused Holocaust museum shooter James von Brunn. Hoover's complaint also cites Beck's October 22, 2007, statement that the 9/11 truth movement consists of &quot;dangerous&quot; &quot;anarchists&quot; who deny the Holocaust and are &quot;the kind of group that Timothy McVeigh would come from.&quot; Alex also talks with Thomas Woods, author of Meltdown: A Free-Market Look at Why the Stock Market Collapsed, the Economy Tanked, and Government Bailouts Will Make Things Worse. Alex covers the news of the day and takes your calls. 

